<h2 class="f24"> 6. Voice Processing Notice:</h2>
<p class="mb-4">This Voice Processing Notice elucidates the procedures through which we collect, utilize, share, retain, and destroy (collectively referred to as "process") the audio recordings you choose to furnish to us, which encompasses your Personal Data. These recordings are utilized for the purpose of crafting a voice model capable of generating synthetic audio resembling your voice (referred to collectively as "Voice Data"), as well as for verifying that the voice featured in the provided audio recordings belongs to you. It's important to note that residents of Illinois and individuals located in Illinois are prohibited from utilizing TextToSpeech’s' voice modeling services.</p>
<h4 class="f20">How TextToSpeech.ai's Voice Modeling Services Work</h4>
<p class="mb-4">TextToSpeech.ai employs advanced voice modeling technology to analyze your audio recordings and generate synthetic audio that closely resembles your voice. When you provide us with recordings of your voice, our proprietary AI-based technologies analyze various speech characteristics to create a unique voice model that captures the nuances of your vocal traits. This voice model serves as a blueprint for generating synthetic audio that mimics your voice.</p>
<p class="mb-4">It's important to note that depending on your location, applicable laws may classify your voice model, along with any synthetic audio generated from it, as a biometric identifier or biometric information.</p>
<h4 class="f20">Use and Disclosure of Your Voice Data</h4>
<p>TextToSpeech.ai processes your audio recordings for the following purposes:</p>
<ol>
    <li><b>Voice Model Development:</b> We utilize your audio recordings to develop a voice model that replicates your voice accurately. This voice model can be used to generate synthetic audio resembling your voice, either at your request or at the request of users on our platform if you opt to make your voice model available in our Voice Library.</li>
    <li><b>Verification: </b>If you utilize our professional voice cloning services, we may use your Voice Data to verify that the voice featured in the provided audio recordings indeed belongs to you.</li>
    <li><b>Mixed Voice Model Creation: </b>Upon your election, we may create a mixed voice model incorporating data from multiple voices.</li>
    <li><b>Research and Development:</b> We utilize Voice Data for research, development, and enhancement of our AI models.</li>
</ol>
<p class="mb-4">TextToSpeech.ai may also disclose your Voice Data to the following entities:</p>
<ul>
    <li><b>Vendors:</b> We may disclose Voice Data to vendors who process the data on our behalf to facilitate the provision of our services to you.</li>
    <li><b>Subsidiaries or Affiliates:</b> Voice Data may be shared with our subsidiaries or affiliates.
</li>
    <li><b>Acquirers, Successors, or Assignees:</b> In the event of an acquisition, succession, or assignment, Voice Data may be disclosed to the acquiring entity, successor, or assignee.
</li>
    <li><b>Applicable Law: </b> We may disclose Voice Data where required by applicable law.</li>
</ul>
<h4 class="f20">Retention Period and Data Deletion</h4>
<p class="mb-4">We retain your Voice Data for the duration necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined above, unless mandated by legal requirements to delete it earlier or to retain it for an extended period (e.g., due to a warrant or subpoena). Upon the conclusion of the retention period, your Voice Data is permanently deleted from our systems.</p>

